record of funding from foundations federal agencies and individual donors we will honor the launch of fse as a full scale research center at fsi's upcoming fall conference redefining security along the food health nexus on november 10 2011 please join me in congratulating roz and her team on this new center's successes and the expectation of many more productive years ahead chip blacker search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest fse director roz naylor lectures on daunting challenges for food security and the environment as part of msu's sustainable michigan endowed program academy october 28 2010 fsi stanford fse news program on food security and the environment to build a global education network on agriculture and the environment july 29 2010 fsi stanford fse news fse releases new book on climate change and food security january 18 2010 fse news program on food security and the environment a climate ripe for high food prices september 22 2008 fsi stanford fse news fsi's new program on food security and the environment tackles global hunger and environmental destruction april 1 2006 fsi stanford fse news gates foundation awards fse and collaborators $3.8 million for the study of biofuels and food security december 3 2007 fsi stanford fse in the news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
